          "@id": "part:186_attP_claim_host_integration_locus"
        }
      ],
      "cat:slug": "186_attP",
      "dcterms:description": "Bacteriophage 186 phage attachment site (attP) for the 186 tyrosine integrase. 307 bp spanning the full attP functional region: Int arm-type recognition sequences on the P (left) and P' (right) arms, a single P-arm IHF site, the tRNA-Ile/attB common core (BOB') with the predicted 7-bp staggered crossover, a right-arm IHF site, and five Apl (recombination directionality factor) operators. 186 is a P2-family lambdoid coliphage; integration into the host chromosome (within the ileY tRNA-Ile locus) requires 186 Int + IHF, while Apl directs excision. Source: NC_001317.1 positions 20867-21173.",
      "dcterms:references": [
        {
          "@id": "https://identifiers.org/pubmed:3011407"
        },
