    {
      "@id": "part:lambda_attP",
      "@type": "sbol:Component",
      "cat:curationStatus": "candidate",
      "cat:documented": false,
      "cat:slug": "lambda_attP",
      "dcterms:description": "Bacteriophage lambda phage attachment site (attP, P-O-P'), the Int/IHF recombination substrate carrying the P and P' arms flanking the 15 bp common core. Identified as attP (NOT bacterial attB) \u2014 its source AY048716.1 is a CRIM integration plasmid (which carries attP), and it shares 192 bp of the P/P' arm region with the genomic lambda attP (a true attB would share only the ~15 bp core). Detailed sub-feature annotation (Int arm/core sites, IHF H/H1/H2, Xis) and functional_claims pending a re-run under the corrected attP identity.",
