      "@type": "sbol:Component",
      "cat:curationStatus": "candidate",
      "cat:documented": false,
      "cat:slug": "phi80_attB",
      "dcterms:description": "Phage phi80 bacterial attachment site attB, within the 3\u2032 end of gene yciI (b1251), divergent from and adjacent to tonB \u2014 reconciling the historical 'tonB region / ~28 min' lore (beside tonB, not in it; not a tRNA gene). 54 bp window from NC_000913.3 containing the 15 bp core consensus AACACTTTCTTAAAT; the exact 17 bp common core and crossover (Leong et al. 1985) are behind paywalls and the precise boundaries are PROVISIONAL. Cognate phage site: phi80_attP.",
