      ],
      "cat:slug": "rrnBT1",
      "dcterms:description": "rrnB T1, the strong intrinsic (Rho-independent) transcription terminator from the T1-T2 terminator cluster downstream of the 5S rRNA gene in the E. coli rrnB ribosomal RNA operon; 169 bp taken at 100% identity from the canonical rrnB operon sequence J01695 (Brosius et al. 1981). Terminates host (E. coli sigma-70) RNA polymerase via a GC-rich hairpin followed by a short U-tract; >97% termination efficiency (Cambray et al. 2013). The element additionally carries a class II conserved sequence (TATCTGTT) that triggers termination by phage (T7/SP6) RNA polymerases independently of the hairpin.",
      "dcterms:references": [
        {
          "@id": "https://identifiers.org/pubmed:7028991"
        },
